		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I was just saying that "IF this THEN do that" is much easier for someone with no computer architecture knowledge to understand than compares, flags, branches and jumps, because the former is just plain old english.</div>
<br />
<br />Oh, this is really true. When I learned a little of QBasic, I was shocked at how straightforward everything was. Like you could just say Print "Blah Blah"
<br />and it would do exactly that. I was used to the old load-and-store loop which was a lot less intuitive I guess than higher level languages are.
<br />
<br />That's QBasic though. C for some reason is a bit harder for me to understand. Just the syntax is weird to me (e.g. "^" is a symbol for either AND,OR, or XOR, while it honestly should be "to the power of". I still don't know how to say "to the power of" in C without doing X*X*X....). And there are terms that I guess I just need to sit down and really figure out what they mean.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
